registerdb:Field.registerdb:Description:
STATIC
If bit[4] is set to 1, 25GR1 channel 0 for AUX MAC IP is enabled, otherwise, this channel is disabled;
If bit[5] is set to 1, 25GR1 channel 1 for AUX MAC IP is enabled, otherwise, this channel is disabled

STATIC
If bit[31] is set to 1, 100GR1 channel 0 for AUX MAC IP is enabled, otherwise, this channel is disabled;
If bit[32] is set to 1, 100GR1 channel 1 for AUX MAC IP is enabled, otherwise, this channel is disabled

TRANS_OK
It will be active when there’s no Bad FCS, Link Fault and Error
tx_status[0]   = frame_tx_ok;
tx_status[1]   = err_fcs;
tx_status[2]   = err_tx_err;
tx_status[3]   = err_par;
tx_status[4]   = fault_local;
tx_status[5]    = fault_remote;
tx_status[7:6] = 2'h0，;
tx_status[8]    = frame_da_unicast;
tx_status[9]   = frame_da_multicast;
tx_status[10] = frame_da_broadcast;
tx_status[11] = 1'h0;
tx_status[12] = frame_type_ctrl;
tx_status[13] = frame_type_pause;
tx_status[14] = frame_type_pfc;
tx_status[15] = frame_type_vlan;
tx_status[16] = frame_type_qinq;
tx_status[19:17] = 3'h0;
tx_status[20] = frame_octets_64;
tx_status[21] = frame_octets_65_127;
tx_status[22] = frame_octets_128_255;
tx_status[23] = frame_octets_256_511;
tx_status[24] = frame_octets_512_1023;
tx_status[25] = frame_octets_1024_1518;
tx_status[26] = frame_octets_1519_max;
tx_status[27] = frame_octets_oversize;
tx_status[31:28] = 4'h0;

